quest.name: Culling the Horde
journal: Eilis bears grim work for an accomplished adventurer.
Eilis informs you that the Sahagin are looking to launch an attack on Tidegate. Slay four of the creatures that prowl near by way of discouragement.
Inform Eilis that you have delayed the advance of the Sahagin front line.
Eilis will rest easier knowing you have kept her nightmare at bay.

dialogue.name: EILIS
dialogue.text: Beyond Tidegate lies the Sahagin Landbase, whence the fishbacks mean to launch an attack.

dialogue.name: EILIS
dialogue.text: Though we cannot forestall their advance, we might give them pause with a sudden strike. I'll need you to make four Sahagin serve as a cautionary tale for the rest.

dialogue.name: EILIS
dialogue.text: A job well done! Let us see how the fishbacks fancy that!

dialogue.name: EILIS
dialogue.text: Each day, the hordes of slimy Sahagin soldiers threaten to take our beloved gates. I pray the day never comes, but prayer alone will not suffice. Thanks to you, today will not be that day.

obj.n: Long Walk off a Short Pier
